#: _generated-doc/main/config/quarkus-narayana-jta.adoc
msgid ""
"icon:lock[title=Fixed at build time] [[quarkus-narayana-jta_quarkus-transaction-manager-unsafe-multiple-last-resources]] [.property-path]##link:#quarkus-narayana-jta_quarkus-transaction-manager-unsafe-multiple-last-resources[[.line-through]#`+++quarkus.transaction-manager.unsafe-multiple-last-resources+++`#]##\n"
"config_property_copy_button:+++quarkus.transaction-manager.unsafe-multiple-last-resources+++[]\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"[.description]\n"
"--\n"
"_This property is deprecated: This property is planned for removal in a future version._\n"
"\n"
"Define the behavior when using multiple XA unaware resources in the same transactional demarcation.\n"
"\n"
"Defaults to `fail`. `warn-each`, `warn-first`, and `allow` are UNSAFE and should only be used for compatibility. Either use XA for all resources if you want consistency, or split the code into separate methods with separate transactions.\n"
"\n"
"Note that using a single XA unaware resource together with XA aware resources, known as the Last Resource Commit Optimization (LRCO), is different from using multiple XA unaware resources. Although LRCO allows most transactions to complete normally, some errors can cause an inconsistent transaction outcome. Using multiple XA unaware resources is not recommended since the probability of inconsistent outcomes is significantly higher and much harder to recover from than LRCO. For this reason, use LRCO as a last resort.\n"
"\n"
"We do not recommend using this configuration property, and we plan to remove it in the future, so you should plan fixing your application accordingly. If you think your use case of this feature is valid and this option should be kept around, open an issue in our tracker explaining why.\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"Environment variable: env_var_with_copy_button:+++QUARKUS_TRANSACTION_MANAGER_UNSAFE_MULTIPLE_LAST_RESOURCES+++[]\n"
"--"
msgstr ""

#: _generated-doc/main/config/quarkus-narayana-jta.adoc
msgid "tooltip:allow[Allow using multiple XA unaware resources in the same transactional demarcation.  This will log a warning once on application startup, but not on each use of multiple XA unaware resources in the same transactional demarcation.], tooltip:warn-first[Allow using multiple XA unaware resources in the same transactional demarcation, but log a warning on the first occurrence.], tooltip:warn-each[Allow using multiple XA unaware resources in the same transactional demarcation, but log a warning on each occurrence.], tooltip:fail[Allow using multiple XA unaware resources in the same transactional demarcation, but log a warning on each occurrence.]"
msgstr ""

#: _generated-doc/main/config/quarkus-narayana-jta.adoc
msgid "tooltip:fail[Allow using multiple XA unaware resources in the same transactional demarcation, but log a warning on each occurrence.]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: _generated-doc/main/config/quarkus-narayana-jta.adoc
#, no-wrap
msgid "About the Duration format"
msgstr "期間フォーマットについて"

#: _generated-doc/main/config/quarkus-narayana-jta.adoc
msgid ""
"To write duration values, use the standard `java.time.Duration` format.\n"
"See the link:https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/17/docs/api/java.base/java/time/Duration.html#parse(java.lang.CharSequence)[Duration#parse() Java API documentation] for more information."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: _generated-doc/main/config/quarkus-narayana-jta.adoc
msgid "You can also use a simplified format, starting with a number:"
msgstr "数字で始まる簡略化した書式を使うこともできます:"

#. type: delimited block =
#: _generated-doc/main/config/quarkus-narayana-jta.adoc
msgid "If the value is only a number, it represents time in seconds."
msgstr "数値のみの場合は、秒単位の時間を表します。"

#. type: delimited block =
#: _generated-doc/main/config/quarkus-narayana-jta.adoc
msgid "If the value is a number followed by `ms`, it represents time in milliseconds."
msgstr "数値の後に `ms` が続く場合は、ミリ秒単位の時間を表します。"

#. type: delimited block =
#: _generated-doc/main/config/quarkus-narayana-jta.adoc
msgid "In other cases, the simplified format is translated to the `java.time.Duration` format for parsing:"
msgstr "その他の場合は、簡略化されたフォーマットが解析のために `java.time.Duration` フォーマットに変換されます："

#. type: delimited block =
#: _generated-doc/main/config/quarkus-narayana-jta.adoc
msgid "If the value is a number followed by `h`, `m`, or `s`, it is prefixed with `PT`."
msgstr "数値の後に `h` 、 `m` 、 `s` が続く場合は、その前に `PT` が付けられます。"

#. type: delimited block =
#: _generated-doc/main/config/quarkus-narayana-jta.adoc
msgid "If the value is a number followed by `d`, it is prefixed with `P`."
msgstr "数値の後に `d` が続く場合は、その前に `P` が付けられます。"
